The blaze broke out before dawn at Hotel Arpit Palace in a congested part of central Delhi. NEW DELHI - At least nine people were killed, and three others injured when a fire engulfed a hotel in New Delhi on Tuesday, a senior official said. The blaze broke out before dawn at Hotel Arpit Palace in a congested part of central Delhi. “Nine people are dead including a woman and a child. Three people are injured,” GC Misra, the director of Delhi Fire Services, told AFP.